locality (
<figureCitation box="[855,922,1702,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1826,1848]" captionTargetBox="[236,1347,193,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[236,1347,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitats of Mesoceration species in South Africa. A) KwaZulu-Natal, uKhahlamba Drakensberg National Park, Injisuthi, stream in Afromontane forest remnant below Van Heyningen’s Pass— M. caniplenum sp. nov., beetles collected from the wet rockface on the right hand side of the stream; B) Western Cape, Matsikammaberg, stream 1 km NW of Sewefontein farm— M. foggoi sp. nov., M. umbrosum; C) Western Cape, Cederberg, Breëwaterkloof stream, ca. 2 km SE of Uitkyk Pass, 1,050 m— M. hirsutum sp. nov., M. dissonum, M. granulovestum, M. jucundum, M. languidum, M. periscopum, M. piceum, M. repandum, M. rivulare; D) Western Cape, Franschhoek Pass, wet rock faces beside stream crossing R 45 road, 500 m— M. rugulosum sp. nov. Photos D. T. Bilton." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243047/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">
Fig. 
<number box="[908,922,1702,1727]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
